(k+1)^2 - 4(2)(2) &= 0 \\
\Rightarrow\qquad k^2 + 2k - 7 &= 0 \\
\Rightarrow\qquad (k+7)(k-1) &= 0 \\
\Rightarrow\qquad k &= -7, \ 1.
\end{align*}

Since $k$ is negative, we have $k = \boxed{-7}$.
